## What is Dependency Injection?

Dependency Injection (DI) is a software design pattern and technique where an object's dependencies (the other objects it needs to function) are provided to it from external sources rather than the object creating them itself. Instead of a class instantiating its dependencies directly, these dependencies are "injected" into the class through constructors, methods, or properties.

